UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2356
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Joseph H.
2 Mattingly, Jr.
3 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was a born in Louisville on August 4, 1932,
4 and was the son of Hubie and Josephine Fleig Mattingly; and
5 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was a valued member of the Loretto
6 community in Marion County, where he operated the Mattingly Funeral Home and,
7 earlier, the Loretto Barber Shop; and
8 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was a dedicated community servant, serving
9 five terms as the Marion County Coroner, as well as serving his country in the United
10 States Army, serving both roles with honor, integrity, and distinction; and
11 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., served God as a faithful member of the Saint
12 Francis of Assisi Church; and
13 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was the loving and beloved husband of
14 Carolyn Masterson Mattingly, to whom he was married 67 years; and
15 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was the loving and beloved father of Donna
16 (Stephen Brady) Mattingly, Joe (Carol) Mattingly, Alan (Cyndi) Mattingly, Norine
17 (Bruce) Masterson, Laura (Wayne) Mitchell, and Gail Boggs; and
18 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was the loving and beloved grandfather of
19 Elizabeth (Aaron) Lanning, Matthew Smith, Christine (Cole) Sinkford, Nicole (Jordan
20 Patterson) Mattingly, Kelly Mattingly, Alex Mattingly, Joseph Mattingly, Eric
21 (Christianne) Masterson, Andrew Masterson, Daniel (Rachael) Masterson, Brooke
22 Mitchell, Blake Mitchell, Katie Boggs, Benjamin Boggs, Abby Boggs, and Josie Boggs;
23 and
24 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., was the loving and beloved great-grandfather
25 of Cooper Burrice, Jack Burrice, Clay Sinkford, Matthew Masterson, Henry Masterson,
26 James Masterson, Patrick Masterson, Noah Masterson, Emmaline Masterson, and Maria
27 Josephine Masterson; and
