UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2356
1 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr. was the loving and beloved brother of Betty
2 Ackermann, Carol Mattingly, Brenda Mattingly, Mary Thornberry, Patsy Clements,
3 Rosie (Michael) Bickett, Nancy Mattingly, Billy (Libby) Mattingly and Lynn (David)
4 Hall; and
5 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr. was the brother of Robert K. Mattingly and
6 David Louis Mattingly, Rita Carol Mattingly, and the father-in-law of David W. Boggs,
7 all of whom preceded him in passing; and
8 WHEREAS, Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., departed this earthly life on February 23,
9 2026;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
12 Kentucky:
13 Section 1. The Senate hereby expresses its most profound sympathy upon the
14 passing of Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr., and extends heartfelt condolences to his family,
15 friends, and community.
16 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
17 memory of Joseph H. Mattingly, Jr.
18 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
19 Resolution to Senator Jimmy Higdon for delivery to the family.
